-- Toyota U.S. sales up 7.7 pct in March
-- 
-- Tue Apr 3, 2007 1:42pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/04/03/us-autos-toyota-sales-idUSN0326091920070403

 

 DETROIT  (Reuters) - Toyota Motor Corp.( 7203.T ) on Tuesday said U.S. sales rose 7.7 percent in March, driven by strong demand for its Prius hybrid. 

 The Japanese automaker, expected to challenge General Motors Corp.( GM.N ) for the top spot in global sales this year, said it sold 242,675 vehicles in the United States in March, up from 217,286 vehicles a year earlier. Toyota said Prius sales rose more than 133 percent to 19,156 units.